### Kaizen API Test File

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000/api
@authToken = your_jwt_token_here

### 1. Get Kaizen Categories
GET {{baseUrl}}/kaizens/categories
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### 2. Get Kaizen Statuses
GET {{baseUrl}}/kaizens/statuses
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### 3. Create a new Kaizen
POST {{baseUrl}}/kaizens
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Reduce Machine Downtime",
  "description": "Implement predictive maintenance to reduce unexpected machine failures",
  "problem_statement": "Machine XYZ experiences frequent unexpected downtime causing production delays",
  "proposed_solution": "Install vibration sensors and implement predictive maintenance schedule",
  "expected_benefits": "Reduce downtime by 40%, increase productivity, reduce maintenance costs",
  "implementation_plan": "1. Purchase sensors 2. Install monitoring system 3. Train staff 4. Implement schedule",
  "category_id": 1,
  "priority": "high",
  "machine_id": 1,
  "division_id": 1,
  "estimated_cost": 5000.00,
  "estimated_savings": 15000.00,
  "estimated_implementation_days": 30
}

### 4. Get all Kaizens
GET {{baseUrl}}/kaizens
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### 5. Get Kaizens with filters
GET {{baseUrl}}/kaizens?status_id=1&category_id=1&priority=high&page=1&limit=10
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### 6. Search Kaizens
GET {{baseUrl}}/kaizens?q=machine&page=1&limit=5
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### 7. Get specific Kaizen by ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/kaizens/1
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### 8. Update Kaizen
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/kaizens/1
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Reduce Machine Downtime - Updated",
  "estimated_cost": 4500.00,
  "actual_cost": 4200.00
}

### 9. Update Kaizen Status
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/kaizens/1/status
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status_id": 3,
  "notes": "Approved for implementation after management review"
}

### 10. Assign Kaizen to User
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/kaizens/1/assign
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "assigned_to": 2,
  "notes": "Assigned to John Doe for implementation"
}

### 11. Add Comment to Kaizen
POST {{baseUrl}}/kaizens/1/comments
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "comment": "Initial assessment looks promising. We should proceed with pilot testing.",
  "is_internal": false
}

### 12. Add Internal Comment
POST {{baseUrl}}/kaizens/1/comments
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "comment": "Budget approved by finance department",
  "is_internal": true
}

### 13. Get Kaizen Comments
GET {{baseUrl}}/kaizens/1/comments
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### 14. Get Kaizen History
GET {{baseUrl}}/kaizens/1/history
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### 15. Get Kaizen Statistics
GET {{baseUrl}}/kaizens/stats
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### 16. Get Kaizens by Machine
GET {{baseUrl}}/kaizens?machine_id=1
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### 17. Get Kaizens by Division
GET {{baseUrl}}/kaizens?division_id=1
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### 18. Get My Submitted Kaizens
GET {{baseUrl}}/kaizens?submitted_by=1
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### 19. Get Kaizens Assigned to Me
GET {{baseUrl}}/kaizens?assigned_to=1
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### 20. Delete Kaizen
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/kaizens/1
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

